text: FET.NAT is a Canadian experimental music group from Gatineau, Quebec,"Quebecois Funk-Punk Quartet Fet.Nat Might Lack Ambition, But Their New 'Le Mal' Doesn't". Exclaim!, March 11, 2019. whose 2019 album Le Mal was shortlisted for the 2019 Polaris Music Prize."Dominique Fils-Aimé, Les Louanges et Elisapie nommés sur la courte liste du prix Polaris". Voir, July 16, 2019. The band consists of vocalist and lyricist JFNO, guitarist Pierre- Luc Clément, saxophonist Linsey Wellman and drummer Olivier Fairfield. Their sound, most commonly categorized as funk-punk,"Fet.Nat: Le Mal". Pitchfork, March 26, 2019. blends aspects of funk and electronic music with avant-garde free jazz. The band previously released the EPs Brunch (2010), Oh! and fuck allure (2012), Purple Empereur (2014) and Poule Mange Poule (2014). ==References== Category:Canadian experimental musical groups Category:Musical groups from Gatineau
